# Rule 2: Unified Data Flow Pipeline

## Core Principle

Data flows through a **standardized 5-phase pipeline**. Components **consume processed data** rather than processing raw data themselves. **ONLY `EnhancedTechnicalIndicators`** can calculate indicators.

---

## 5-Phase Pipeline (Phases 1-5)

```
PHASE 1: DATA INGESTION
├── Component: ClickHouseDataManager
├── Input: Symbol list, date range, timeframe
└── Output: pd.DataFrame[timestamp, open, high, low, close, volume]
                                    ↓
PHASE 2: INDICATORS LAYER
├── Component: EnhancedTechnicalIndicators
├── Input: Raw OHLCV DataFrame
├── Output: OHLCV + 29 indicators (SMA, RSI, MACD, ADX, ATR, etc.)
└── ⭐ ONLY HERE can indicators be calculated
                                    ↓
PHASE 3: FEATURE ENGINEERING
├── Component: EnhancedFeatureEngineer
├── Input: OHLCV + Indicators DataFrame
└── Output: OHLCV + Indicators + 50+ ML features
                                    ↓
PHASE 4: SIGNAL GENERATION
├── Component: EnhancedSignalGenerator
├── Input: Feature-enriched DataFrame
└── Output: Fully enriched DataFrame + signal columns
                                    ↓
PHASE 5: STRATEGY LAYER
├── Component: Trading Strategies (10 implementations)
├── Input: Fully Enriched DataFrame
├── Output: List[StrategySignal]
└── ⭐ Strategies MUST consume enriched data, NOT calculate indicators
                                    ↓
           → TO RULE 3: PHASE 6 (Risk Authorization)
```

---

## Component Responsibility Matrix

| Phase | Component | Can Calculate Indicators? | Responsibility |
|-------|-----------|--------------------------|----------------|
| 1 | DataManager | ❌ NO | Load data from DB |
| 2 | Indicators Engine | ✅ YES (ONLY HERE) | Calculate indicators |
| 3 | Feature Engineer | ❌ NO | Engineer features |
| 4 | Signal Generator | ❌ NO | Generate preliminary signals |
| 5 | Strategy | ❌ NO | Apply strategy logic |

